{
  "name": "Locus: Utterance",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature. The properties of this item are affixed to an item.)</em></p><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>This locus was previously in the position of Hormuz the Ensorcellite of the Fallen Queen. It was affixed to his face cover.</p><p>While attuned, the Utterance magically merges with an <strong>item</strong> of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, requires 10 minutes to complete and it upon completion it exaggerates the natural lines and contours of the item. Once completed, if applied to a weapon it becomes magical for the purpose of overcoming resistances.</p><p><strong>Effect: </strong>The attuned creature cannot have their voice silenced, as their voice pierces effects like the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.TsXoAnsMto2MIufg]{Silence} spell, making it possible for them to cast while under the effect. Additionally, it is impossible for others to read their lips when speaking. Lastly, they are able to cast @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.WetkOdbiRlbohGQ6]{Thaumaturgy} as a <strong>Bonus Action</strong> but only to increase the volume of their voice.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
